HEADWORD: Drumming
<hw>Drum"ming</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of beating
upon, or as if upon, a drum; also, the noise which the male of the
ruffed grouse makes in spring, by beating his wings upon his
sides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

